Step 1: Identify the cost of goods sold (COGS) from the income statement. 
  COGS = 3,020,000.00

Step 2: Determine the inventory values from the balance sheet.
  Initial Inventory (2023-12-31) = 0.00
  Ending Inventory (2024-01-27) = 440,000.00

Step 3: Calculate the average inventory.
  Average Inventory = (Initial Inventory + Ending Inventory) / 2
  Average Inventory = (0.00 + 440,000.00) / 2 = 220,000.00

Step 4: Compute the Inventory Turnover Ratio.
  Inventory Turnover Ratio = COGS / Average Inventory
  = 3,020,000.00 / 220,000.00 ≈ 13.73

Thus, the Inventory Turnover Ratio is approximately 13.73.
